               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Ṣalota nǝssǝḥa 
 II) Śǝrʿāta qǝddāse "Ordinary of the Mass" (fols.
                     10rb-36va)
 III) Anaphoras (fols. 36vb-86vb)
 III-1) Anaphora of the
                     Apostles (fols. 36vb-47vb)
 III-2) Anaphora of Our Lord Jesus Christ (fols.
                     47vb-53vb)
 III-3) Anaphora of Our Lady by St Cyriacus of Behnesa (fols.
                     53vb-71va)
 III-4) Anaphora of St Jacob of Serug (fols. 71va-82rb)
                     III-5) Anaphora of St Dioscorus of Alexandria (fols. 82rb-86vb)
 
                     Additio 1.</summary>
